other_tests.findings: The appendix is enlarged at 9 mm and has wall hyperenhancement with surrounding mild fat stranding without evidence of perforation. No appendicolith can be seen. The rest of the small bowel and colon are without focal lesions or colon wall thickening. There are scattered hypodensities in the liver that are too small to characterize, but the liver is normal in shape without ascites. The pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, urinary bladder, and distal ureters are normal. There is no evidence of abdominal aortic aneurysm or retroperitoneal and mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
